# Commit conventions — ConciergeTravel.fr

We follow [Conventional Commits](https://www.conventionalcommits.org/) with project-specific scopes.

## Format

```
<type>(<scope>): <short summary>

<optional body>

<optional footer(s)>
```

## Types
- `feat`: new feature
- `fix`: bug fix
- `chore`: tooling, scaffolding, dependency bumps
- `refactor`: refactor without behavior change
- `perf`: performance improvement
- `docs`: documentation only
- `test`: tests only
- `style`: formatting, no logic
- `revert`: revert previous commit

## Scopes (project-specific)
- `repo` — root tooling, CI, monorepo plumbing
- `web` — `apps/web`
- `admin` — `apps/admin`
- `db` — `packages/db`
- `domain` — `packages/domain`
- `integrations` — generic integrations changes
- `amadeus`, `little`, `makcorps`, `apify`, `gplaces`, `brevo`, `algolia`, `redis`, `sentry` — specific integration
- `seo`, `geo`, `aeo`, `jsonld`, `sitemap`, `robots`, `llms`
- `booking`, `search`, `loyalty`, `pricing`, `editorial`, `account`, `auth`, `email`
- `ui` — shared UI
- `docs` — documentation
- `skills` — `.cursor/skills/`

## Examples

```
feat(booking): persist cancellation policy verbatim in bookings table

fix(amadeus): refresh OAuth token on 401 with mutex to avoid stampede

docs(seo): document anti-cannibalisation 301 matrix

chore(repo): bump turbo to 2.5.0 and pnpm to 10.33.2

feat(skills): bootstrap 29 cursor skills covering CDC v3.0 §14

refactor(domain): extract Booking state machine into dedicated module
```

## Rules
- Subject in imperative mood ("add", "fix", not "added", "fixes").
- ≤ 72 chars subject line; body wraps at 100 chars.
- Reference ADRs in body when relevant: `Refs: docs/adr/0003-payload-cms.md`.
- Breaking changes flagged with `!` and `BREAKING CHANGE:` footer.
